        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 3:18PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 318 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Brooks Crossroads, or near Yadkinville, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Wilkesboro...
Yadkinville...
Jonesville...
Boonville...
East Bend...
Boomer...
and King.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
north central and northwestern North Carolina...and southwestern
Virginia.</instruction>
